This International Trans visibility day let's accept our differences and celebrate our 'selves'

Mohini; the deception or the truth, the divine or the derogatory. An avatar once of scaredness beyond binaries, today is the perversion of artistry. The slayer of demons once, today is seen as flaw of life
Life becomes a stage, tarnished by the expectations of the society
Such is the irony

We will prevail coerced or perhaps some of us perish, lest our truth becomes the ultimate weapon. 

An encore to our truth, the divinity of our selves
Today we look into the brittle mirror, glue shattered ironies
Today we widen our umbrella; celebrate the selves in us, preach that is nothing but acceptance, live that is all our uniqueness. 
Today we shall slay with love, gratitude and reform
Today we become whole, to make the world whole
Mohini shall prevail and all will hail

latestIgtvVideos.title: Heal the world #samaajscope @shazamorani @samaajscope
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Although the human race is going through a difficult time right now, the environment is healing. We can all see the benefits with our own eyes - cleaner air, lower noise pollution, flora & fauna blooming! This once again proves what we’ve known all along. We have been a roadblock in the planet’s journey to recovery.
We cannot continue the way we were before. Change is impossible without commitment, and this is a wake up call - WE NEED TO CHANGE. 
With #TheSamaajScopeChallenge we’re asking you to name three changes that you are going to commit to, that will contribute to continued social & environmental growth. 
Post a video on Instagram & tag as many friends you like to encourage them to do the same. 
Don’t forget to tag @samaajscope as well! Let’s work together & share ideas!

Posted @withregram • @thezeenataman Just a little skit for ILEM JAPAN on the beauty of authenticity! 

There is so much to admire about the Japanese culture of meticulous minimalism, functionality, and well-being. Then there’s the fact that I’m a committed herbal tea drinker, and I love the clean and bold flavours of ILEM JAPAN’s green teas. After meals before bed, on an empty stomach, at the first hint of a cold… the electric kettle is always on the boil at my home. 

So you see, this collaboration was a no brainer. Here’s a Japanese company built by an Indian girl @ishvanipatel who grew up in Japan and now wants to serve people across the globe! 
The intent? To help Improve Longevity and Enhance Mindfulness. ILEM! Get it?! 

Anyway, you and I both know that imitations and copies can be a dime a dozen, but nothing ever matches up to an “OG”.

#ILEMJAPAN #JapaneseTea #GreenTea #MadeInJapan
